You are given two strings s and t.

String t is generated by random shuffling string s and then add one more letter at a random position.

Return the letter that was added to t.

Example 1:

Input: s = "abcd", t = "abcde"
Output: "e"
Explanation: 'e' is the letter that was added.


Approach : 1) convert string to char array then sort it then compare char to char if the char of arr1 is not equals to char of arr then return the char of arr1.
handle the out of bound exception using the exception e. return the 's' to handle the edge case if there is no element in both the arrays.

2)taking the int sum; iterating over the string length adding chars to the sum using charAt from string t later on removing the chars present in string s returning the remaining.




class Solution {
    public char findTheDifference(String s, String t) {
    //    char[] arr = s.toCharArray();
    //    char[] arr1 = t.toCharArray();
    //    Arrays.sort(arr);
    //    Arrays.sort(arr1);
    //    for(int i=0;i<arr1.length;i++){
    //       try {
    //         if (arr[i] != arr1[i]) {
    //             return arr1[i];
    //         }
    //     } catch (Exception e) {
    //         // TODO: handle exception
    //         return arr1[i];
    //     }
       
    // }
    //  return 's'; 

    int sum =0;
    for(int i=0;i<t.length();i++){
        sum+=t.charAt(i);
    }
    for(int i=0;i<s.length();i++){
        sum-=s.charAt(i);
    }
    return (char)sum;
}
}
